Casting a furtive glance round the laboratory, and shrugging his shoulders, Baldred departed;
     and Flapdragon having bathed the sufferer’s temples with the decoction, in obedience to his
     master’s injunctions, turned to inquire what he should do next.

“Well, I am glad to find you have got the use of your arm again,” observed the iron-merchant;
     “but I can’t say you look so well as when you left us. You seem paler—eh? what do you think,
     Ebba?”

“For the first, you are called Auriol Darcy,” replied Rougemont; “for the second, you are
     living in the reign of his most Catholic Majesty James I. of England, and Sixth of Scotland;
     and for the third, I trust you will soon recover your reason.”
